   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Q1. Why do Decision Trees overfit?\n",
    "👉 Because:\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "They keep splitting until pure\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Capture noise\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Solution:\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Pruning\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Limit depth\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Q2. What is Information Gain?\n",
    "👉 Reduction in entropy after split\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Q3. Why don’t we use Decision Trees directly in production often?\n",
    "👉 Because:\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "High variance\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Unstable\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Use:\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Random Forest\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Gradient Boosting\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Q4. Can Decision Trees handle missing values?\n",
    "👉 Yes (some implementations):\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Surrogate splits\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Imputation\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Q5. Are Decision Trees affected by feature scaling?\n",
    "👉 ❌ No\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Because they use splits, not distance\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Q6. What is the difference between Random Forest and Decision Tree?\n",
    "👉 Random Forest:\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Ensemble of trees\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Reduces overfitting\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Q7. What happens if you increase tree depth?\n",
    "👉 Training accuracy ↑\n",
    "👉 Overfitting ↑\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Q8. What is leaf node?\n",
    "👉 Final output node (prediction)\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Q9. How does a tree choose the best split?\n",
    "👉 Based on:\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Gini\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Entropy\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Q10. When would you NOT use Decision Trees?\n",
    "👉 When:\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Data is very small\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Need high generalization\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Linear relationship is enough\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "🚀 Final Interview Answer (Perfect Summary)\n",
    "👉 “Decision trees use impurity measures like entropy and Gini to split data. They tend to overfit, which can be controlled using pruning techniques. While simple and interpretable, they are often combined into ensemble methods for better performance.”\n",
    "\n",
